<p>
  Together, the Myrick, Lee, and Brittain lines converge in this chapter as a single lived
  reality. They form the backdrop of childhood memories, family visits, and stories passed
  across generations. Chapter 5 thus marks the transition from ancestral movement to personal
  memory—from the long road that brought the family west to the places and people that shaped
  John’s own sense of who he was and where he came from.
</p>
